observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Mayor create an inventory team composed of representatives from the OCA and GSD who shall: (a) conduct inventory of all PPE;
(b) prepare inventory report; (c) prepare and update property records such as PPELCs and PCs; (d) reconcile the balance of PPE in the books and Inventory Report; and (e) come up with the fair values of the PPE items with undetermined values.
We also recommended that Management require the GSD to: (a) undertake the physical count of inventories and reconcile the actual count against the accounting records to establish the validity and accuracy of reported balances and submit RPCI regularly to the Auditor concerned pursuant to Sec. 124 Volume I of the NGAS not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively; and (b) strengthen controls over the inventory requiring the personnel in charge to regularly reconcile their respective records on all inventory accounts so that any discrepancy is immediately verified and adjusted.

The management should:

1. Give highest priority to the remittance of all premium contributions and loan payments;
2. Request from Pag-IBIG for reconciliation of premium and loan accounts to settle the differences and to establish the correct amount that should be paid or remitted;
3. Refund each employee who availed of the loans and who were deducted of premium contribution once the correct amount has been established; and
4. Conduct further in-depth analysis and monitoring of these accounts so that necessary adjustments be recorded for fair presentation in the financial statements.

